<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-03-28a.107.0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100779" speakername="Lord Drayson" colon=":" colnum="107"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60328w02.htm#60328w02_spmin0">
	<p pid="a.107.0/1">We have not taken any action.</p>
	<p pid="a.107.0/2">The Royal Navy did not operate any anti-submarine sonar during the NATO exercise off southern Spain between 24&ndash;<phrase class="date" code="2006-01-26">26 January</phrase>. Furthermore, there is no current evidence to show that Royal Naval sonar has ever been responsible for whale strandings.</p>
</reply>
